casebody.data:
Mickey and Nell SWINBURN, Plaintiffs-Appellants, v. FIRST FEDERAL SAVINGS AND LOAN OF LUBBOCK, TEXAS, and Bob Zirby, Lubbock, Texas, Defendants-Appellees. No. 73-2635. United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 23, 1973. Mickey Swinburn, pro se. Bill D. Tucker, Lubbock, Tex., for defendants-appellees.

Before WISDOM, AINSWORTH and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

The appeal is ordered dismissed for want of prosecution for appellant’s failure to file a brief within the time fixed by the rules. Rule 9(b). See Tidwell v. Dees, 5 Cir. 1972, 464 F.2d 1297.
